<br>
Greed is NEVER a correct reason. The Bushes are GREEDY. They are small minded, absent moraled people.<br>
<br>
It is wrong to ask Americans to die for small minded reasons and people. It is wrong to order American Soldiers to die for greed.<br>
<br>
As for the election, the big beef for a LOT of Americans is that:<br>
<br>
a) there is proof that minority voters were disenfranchised AFTER voting. (votes in black districts were not recounted where they were in white districts, this was by order of an election commissioner appointed by Jeb Bush... I think you can see why this is suspicious)<br>
<br>
b) there was proof NATIONWIDE that there was voter fraud on BOTH sides.<br>
<br>
c) that because of these two situations, that there was not a runoff election in the disputed areas.<br>
<br>
d) finally, Bush lost the popular vote. While there has in fact been SEVERAL elections where the electoral college, for one reason or another, voted in favor of an unpopular president, it has NOT happened in the information age. <br>
<br>
Everyone who reads this board is at least somewhat computer savvy. You really must recognise that this DOES change everything, perceptionwise.<br>
<br>
NEITHER major party candidate won a majority. However, somehow, despite the fact that the majority of Americans voted for Liberal Candidates (note the plural), we wound up with a Conservative President. I am neither, but this BOTHERS me. This does NOT represent democracy or a democratic or republican system of government. Many people feel that the majority of the vote should represent the WILL of the voters. In this situations, the test came back with the will of the voters FALSELY showing that a majority wanted a conservative. Yet, through a hiccup in our election system (IMO, an outdated one), we were given this conservative president.<br>
<br>
My final notes:<br>
<br>
I didn't like Clinton. He was a philanderer, he was a liar,  and he was greedy. There is some proof that he may have commited an unforgivable crime (rape) and that he may have been in a 'marriage of convenience' (another thing i find utterly distasteful)<br>
<br>
I didn't like Bush Senior. He wasn't all that competent, he was a liar, the worst sort of polician, and he was (and is) greedy.<br>
<br>
I don't like G W Bush. He is a liar (multiply proven), he is crass, he is a cad, he is greedy, he is a LEGACY. We don't need legacy presidents in the USA. We have enough qualified people out there that we don't need some senator or former presidents sons running for office.<br>
<br>
We don't have aristocracy and we don't need aristocracy. We are founded on better things than this. George W Bush acts like an aristocrat and this bothers me deeply. Gore bothers me for the SAME reason.<br>
<br>
As for impeachment... do you REALLY think that Enron would have been swept under the rug if we were not still recovering from 9-11? Seriously... Cheney and Bush sold access to national policymaking in to persons who earned the money illegaly. Since then, they have refused investigation and access to the evidence.<br>
<br>
Influence peddling (an impeachable offense)<br>
Corruption (they accepted ill gained proceeds)<br>
Obstruction of Justice (not necc impeachable, but prosecutable after an impeachment)<br>
<br>
This makes 3 scumbag presidents in a row as far as I'm concerned... we need new blood. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4>The Soapbox</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.9.5.4<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

